messages.message:
Brian
That's one thing I like about being married. You don't feel weird talking to other adults. Single or married. One friend called Iga and I the power couple. Now I have books to back it up.

Brian
Flatland, Atlas Shrugged (I'm Riordan apparently), 48 laws of power, the trusted advisor, hired by Lou Adler, all of Malcolm Gladwell, the future is made not managed by Reddit founder
Telepsychics
ooo

Brian
The lean startup, disrupted, I am building my social network and coming out from under my rock.  I am sick of Banks. I am sick of time wasters in politics. I am sick of economics. But there is only one solution, start solving more problems. I need this calendar to keep track of it all.
You go!

Brian
I need help
With what?

Brian
Well whether or not to use this calendar for one. But you already answered that. I also need a job and friends.

friends!
they're overrated!
Iga is your friend. One night a week pretend you dont have electricity (or a phone battery!) and do something fun, like a game or some exercise or some art or some star gazing
Have you heard of Quota? I think you'd like it

Brian
We do that.

Brian
I can't spend all day berating you with messages, but I wanted to drop this.  You are absolutely right about pretending there no power and here is the science saying the same thing.
http://m.slashdot.org/story/316889
Going offline for 24 hours a week significantly improves health
Slashdot
m.slashdot.org

Oh cool
And dont worry about berating
Brian

If I'm busy, I won't reply, but I'm usually not that busy at work
I regularly chat with friends during work hours

Brian
I need robots in the cloud to help copy data on to my calendar. All these fucking companies are taking too long to work together.
Are you still into TV show watching?

Brian
New episodes of South Park lol, Late show with Colbert, Treehouse masters, lots of youtube and news sources.  I watch a lot of movies too, it's been less since therapy last week.
I remember being all up into shows

Brian
I have to moderate better.  Working from home allowed me to have a constant distraction.

I stopped though, I started finding them not worth my time, or like I couldnt fit them in since I had so much other stuff to do (the calendar stuff)
Now that my life is more chill and I'm married, I'm finding myself on Netflix more and more
I'm worried I'll become a potato

Brian
I watch them specifically so that I can multitask, watching something and doing my calendar and journaling has been working for me.  I can take in multiple conversations at the same time.  I am wondering if I could learn to give such great interview that I can talk to two interviewers at the same time.

interesting
wait, so you cant watch something and work and totally be aware of both?

Brian
I watch multiple youtube videos at a time and switch between focusing on them.  I can switch focus quickly because I practice.

Neato
I just listen to podcasts and work at the same time... It's nice

Brian
Yeah that is a good idea.
Can you listen to two at a time?

No, that would be islly
I havent tried, but Im guessing that would be a mess
I hate it when coworkers give me shitty food
I hate it when coworkers talk to me but I dont want them to talk to me and in my head I'm like "dont care dont care dont care" but outwardly I'm like "uh-huh, oh, yeah, I see"

Brian
I don't have coworkers but when I do I am going to pretend like I trust them and use them as tools to send me positive energy.
haha good idea

Brian
I nailed 2 interviews today.

lets hope the negative energy of you pretending doesn't counteract their positive energy.
Oh nice, for what?

Brian
HEAT software and Orion Health.  PNNL and general dynamics is in process.
Also I won the hearts of at least 3 recruiters and one I get personal representation.
psychopaths are really good at winning hearts

Brian
Ha. I am being sincere though. I am just teasing for efficiency.

Brian
I am social networking like an AI with a conscience.

Brian
You're a good person.
Well thanks!

Brian
Can you do me a favor?
Potentially

Brian
  Can you pick one of our mutual friends maybe David Smith and send him a message like "You are so smart!"
I suppose!

Brian
Yes!  It's working!
That's silly

Brian
Is it though?  Is it really though?
To me, yes

Brian
lol, it is silly to me too.  But I have always acted like a child on the internet.  This is just a test, and you are helping.
All I said was "hi" to Travis

Brian
Aww, not enough, tell him he looks smart today.
If this works it will be a hilarious inside joke.
Imagine you aren't the only person that is going to tell him that right now.
lol
I'll send you the results.
lol
Too silly, I refuse

Brian
Aww come on!
You think its silly because you know the truth
Travis is going to think what?

"well that was weird and out of the blue"
"must be doing one of those 'I'm going to give out hardly thoughtful compliments to make me and the world feel better, hehe' thing"

Brian
What?
He said that?
No. I'm guessing

Brian
lol cynic.

Brian
We should do Joe Flieger next.
No, that would be silly

Brian
Will you send him a compliment?
No that would be silly

Brian
Stinker
Sure

Brian
Are you still afraid of being silly and looking people straight in the eyes?

Im not afraid of being silly
and I am still, though must less so, afraid of looking people straight in the eyes.

Brian
Hmmm.  I wonder if these are related
I dont think they are

Brian
ok
Can't give someone a compliment?  Who are you right now?
I dont give people compliments just for the sake of giving them a compliment. It's not very genuine.

Brian
I think you don't give enough people compliments in general.  I also think you can't take a compliment, because I asked 40 other people to give a compliment, you are the only person that said No.  1 other person cried because she has a problem with worrying and she is crazy.  2 out of 40 was my success rate, you are a mathematician, what is your rate of success?
It's not my personality to give compliments. I'm not going to give an out-of-the-blue ingenuine one just because someone tells me to.

Brian
Can you do anything people tell you to?
If I feel it makes sense to, sure

Brian
God tells you to give compliments.

He does?
I'll pass

Brian
You're passing on God's word?  You should talk to your husband about that

I dont think God tells me to give compliments
And if he does, then yes, I'll pass
Because he, of all people, would understand

Brian
I think this is a sign why you have a problem with religion.  Here is proof  http://bible.knowing-jesus.com/topics/Compliments
15 Bible verses about Compliments
A topical Bible which shows the most relevant Bible verse for each topic
bible.knowing-jesus.com
Act like God and you will feel more like him.

uh... "He who rebukes a man will afterward find more favor Than he who flatters with the tongue." "A lying tongue hates those it crushes, And a flattering mouth works ruin."
but anyway, I dont think God commands us to compliment. thats not what any of these verses are saying.
Commandment #11 "thou shalt compliment thy friend each day"

Brian
To me your are Perfect.
gross

Brian
You just made a commandment, who else can do that?
Alright, Love Actually.

Brian
Spread the love sister!
How did your interviews end up?

Brian
Awesome.  Interview with PNNL in 30 minutes, I am so excited.  Thank you for asking!    I had 4 interviews today so I am already kind of tired.  Good thing my boss is giving me some slack.

I thought youdidn't have a boss.
Like that's the point of the interviews, you know?
4 interviews... that's so many!! Nice

Brian
Yeah, he is done paying me Saturday.  He will give me a few hours here and there but I've been in so much therapy I owe him a few weeks for free.
Good luck, you'll find something!

Brian
I believe so too!  If not can you get me a job with the Provost?
Aw. Sorry! We have no openings, and I have no say!

Brian
Oh thank you!  Let me know if you figure out who to ask
so what's up?

Brian
Talking to this profoundly intelligent lady about the meaning of life.
oh ok cool, carry on

Brian
Whats up with you?
listening to a zombie podcast and trying to figure out today's definition of "faculty"

Brian
lol does that definition change often?

Brian
Can I see a report?
Maybe,

Who am I reaching out to?

Brian
Just curious.

I recall you saying you asked 40 other people to give compliments
I can't be the only one that's rekindled

Brian
Probably not.

Brian
Here is my ambition, train AI to be kind to people.  By connecting with the people around me, you all hold me accountable to that dream.  Did you find me a job in Flagstaff, please?  Iga wants us to move there and I don't see any possibilities.
Fuck, I could hardly find myself a job in Flagstaff

Brian
Now you understand how hard this is for me.  I appreciate your help regardless.  Thank you for your time
Now that party seems overkill

Brian
http://asgardia.space/concept
What are you doing?

Brian
Collecting knowledge off the project I am working on so I can actively teach course.studysauce.com in context to everyone.
I am faster than the internet.
I figured it all out.

No you aren't
Are you having a manic episode?

Brian
That is so strange me Psychologist called me manic!
I'll give you an example.

Brian
Let's use the stock market.  In NYC there is a person or a computer purchasing stocks from a company in London.  If I make friends with both of them and communicate at the same time, I will understand their decision making process before the computers that the program on makes the money transfer.  I can absorb their knowledge and use it before they can use it to compete with each other.

Maybe if your psychologist said that, you should listen?
There are pills for that

Brian
Wow, that is a terrible idea, thank you though.  I am not into drugs.

And if it's true, it may seem great now...
But it'll come crashing down
So I hope it's not mania
And that you are just being odd

Brian
They said its mania.  Already came crashing down.  Now I can wield it.
But it crashes down into depression

Brian
I cry every morning for practice.  I knew Wells Fargo was going to take a shit on itself before most people.
Mania shouldn't go untreated

Brian
How do you treat it?
Pills, exercise, therapy

Brian
Which pills just for future reference?

Mood stabilizers, anti-psychotics, anti-depressants
Like abilify, or wellbutrin, or Lamictal

Brian
Yup, heard of that one.  I appreciate you a lot for this.  I can tell you really care

Brian
How are you feeling?

A little bummed for oversleeping
I have to go to the laundromat and I'm putting it off!

Brian
Good.  Laundry is a waste of time.

Brian
I just need a few good reasons to do or not to do something.  1 reason for not taking lamictal is the risk of a deadly skin side effect.  I know how personally you take this.  All my other exes are dropping like flies because I am killing people with kindness.  I hope that doesn't happen here.  You are extremely smart to me.
K
What's your number?
K. Probably won't call you

Brian
I hope you do when you think the moment is right.

Brian
Everything is going to happen anyways so it doesn't matter. Just me saying I hope to express that you can always have an open line of communication if you need it
Any interview results?

Greetings earthling.

Well, I remember that time a long time ago when you were teaching me how to use php.

Brian

For a website

Brian
Can you use Angular2 instead?

Brian
What is the goal of the site?

Well, I need a user to be able to submit a form, and then the form input needs to be either sent to an email or (probably preferably) sent to some database.
I feel there are different approaches required (php or jquery/ajax, I dont know) depending on which of those two I want to do. So I should figure that out first!
I need to talk to Travis about it. But for now, I must go run.
I need to talk to Travis about it. But for now, I must go run.

Brian
You need an HTTP server running to serve web pages locally.  Node has modules that are easy to use that handle HTTP.  PHP needs a web server like Apache or nginx.  Here is a repository with a Docker file and PHP script https://github.com/megamindbrian/docker-php-starter
megamindbrian/docker-php-starter
docker-php-starter - Boilerplate for docker and PHP
github.com

this is quite much for me! I know I can figure it out but I just need to start from super beginner level

Brian
Are you using Windows 10?

Brian
Ok, I recommend Docker for local development.  After you get something running you can pick out where to host it so it is accessible for anyone.
Can I call a web server, or do I have to have something downloaded locally when I'm developing my pages locally?

Brian
Docker is best because it runs as a process locally.  If you want to upload in between every edit there are hosts that allow for that.
